#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:1
msgid "World > PhysicsWorld"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:3
msgid ""
"`PhysicsWorld` extends the regular world with a `pymunk` space. Use it when "
"actors should fall, collide, bounce, or be connected with joints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:5
msgid ""
"Install `miniworlds_physics` alongside `miniworlds` and import it from the "
"separate package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:28
msgid "Typical Physics Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:30
msgid "`world.gravity` controls global acceleration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:31
msgid "`world.damping` slows bodies over time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:32
msgid ""
"`actor.physics.simulation` chooses how an actor participates: `simulated`, "
"`manual`, `static`, or `None`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:33
msgid ""
"`actor.physics` also exposes `density`, `friction`, `elasticity`, "
"`shape_type`, and velocity helpers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:35
msgid "Collision Hooks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:37
msgid ""
"Physics worlds support dedicated actor callbacks such as "
"`on_touching_circle` and `on_separation_from_circle`. These receive the "
"other actor and contact information from the physics engine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:39
msgid ""
"See also the [Flappy Bird tutorial](../patterns/flappy_physics.md) for a "
"larger example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:41
msgid "Runtime Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:43
msgid ""
"Physics support is intentionally separate from the main `miniworlds` "
"package. Desktop Python environments are the recommended target. Browser-"
"based runtimes such as Pyodide/H5P may not provide the same physics package "
"support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:47
msgid "API Reference"
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds_physics.physics_world.PhysicsWorld:1 of
msgid ""
"A PhysicsWorld is a playing field on which objects follow physical laws."
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds_physics.physics_world.PhysicsWorld:3 of
msgid ""
"The PhysicsWorld itself defines some values with which the physics engine "
"can be influenced, e.g. the gravity in the world."
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds_physics.physics_world.PhysicsWorld:6 of
msgid ""
"All actors on a PhysicsWorld have an attribute ``actor.physics``, with which "
"you can change the physical properties of the object."
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds_physics.physics_world.PhysicsWorld.accuracy:1 of
msgid "Sets number of physics-steps performed in each frame."
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds_physics.physics_world.PhysicsWorld.accuracy:3 of
msgid "Default: 1"
msgstr ""

